Failing test:
  REQ-011 / PROP-003 / PROP-022: nextAvailableNoteId pure helper
  > REQ-011: no collision suffix for empty existingIds

Root cause: test assertion `expect(resultStr).not.toMatch(/-\d+$/)` is
internally inconsistent with spec REQ-011 which mandates the format
`YYYY-MM-DD-HHmmss-SSS`. The milliseconds segment `-SSS` (e.g., `-000`)
always ends with `/-\d+$/`, making the regex fire on the base format itself
rather than only on the collision suffix `-N`. Implementation faithfully
matches the spec format. The other collision tests use hardcoded IDs
(`"2026-04-28-120000-000"`) that do not collide with the actual computed
base for timestamp 1714298400000 (`"2024-04-28-100000-000"`), so they pass.

Phase 4 finding: test `step4-initialize-capture.test.ts:337` assertion
`not.toMatch(/-\d+$/)` is faulty — should use a more specific regex like
`not.toMatch(/-\d{1,5}$/)` (small N suffix only) or `/^[0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{6}-[0-9]{3}$/`
(exact base format). Route to Phase 2a for test correction.

